---
import Layout from '@layouts/Layout.astro';
import Footer from '@components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Support | RHT: Reading Habit Tracker"
  description="Get help with RHT, the Reading Habit Tracker mobile app."
>
  <main class="page-wrap">
    <a href="/rht" class="back-link">&larr; Back to RHT</a>

    <h1>Support</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Need help? We're here for you.</p>

    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>How do I log my reading?</h3>
      <p>
        Tap "I read today" on the Today screen. That's the whole loop: one tap
        per day. Your streak, heatmap, and stats update from there.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>I forgot to log a day. Can I fix it?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes. Go to Activity, switch to Month, and tap any past day to mark it as
        read. Tap a marked day to remove it. Your history is always yours to
        edit.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>What are monthly recaps?</h3>
      <p>
        At the start of each month, RHT shows a recap of the month that ended:
        days read, longest run, and books finished. Past recaps stay available
        forever via "View recap" on each month card in Activity.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>How do I add books?</h3>
      <p>
        Use the Search tab to find books via Open Library (this needs an
        internet connection), then add them to your shelf. Everything else about
        your shelf works offline.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Where is my data stored?</h3>
      <p>
        All your reading data is stored locally on your device. There is no
        account and no cloud sync. You can export everything as a JSON file from
        Settings, and deleting the app deletes your data.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Does the app work offline?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes. Logging, streaks, heatmaps, recaps, and your shelf all work
        offline. Only book search and cover images need a connection.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>How do app updates work?</h3>
      <p>
        Bug fixes arrive automatically. You can also pull the latest fixes
        yourself: Settings, then "Get the latest bug fixes".
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      If you have questions, feedback, or need help with something not covered
      above, please reach out:
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="mailto:amanmittal.work@gmail.com">amanmittal.work@gmail.com</a>
    </p>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style is:global>
  body {
    background: linear-gradient(
      180deg,
      #fce8c9 0%,
      #fdf6eb 35%,
      #ffffff 100%
    ) !important;
  }
</style>

<style>
  .page-wrap {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 40px 24px 40px;
    font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;
    color: #1d1d1f;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: #6e6e73;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .back-link:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
    color: #1d1d1f;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 6px;
    letter-spacing: -0.3px;
  }

  .subtitle {
    color: #6e6e73;
    font-size: 15px;
    margin: 0 0 32px;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 32px 0 12px;
    color: #1d1d1f;
  }

  .faq-item {
    border: 1px solid #ead9bd;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    background: #fff;
    box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04);
  }

  .faq-item h3 {
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 6px;
    color: #1d1d1f;
  }

  .faq-item p {
    margin: 0;
    color: #6e6e73;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  p {
    color: #6e6e73;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  a {
    color: #b45309;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  a:hover {
    color: #92400e;
  }
</style>
